snippet.textDisplay:
Huh... So much goodness, but there's also so much I question.

I can't tell what the movie is about. The first Wonder Woman was about war, and it's nature. Aquaman was about responsibility, both personal and with family. Shazam was very much about the experience of having to growing up before you're ready. From the trailer, I can't tell what this movie is really about thematically. I can tell some of the plot points... I can see some of what happens, but that's not the same thing.

Still, Wonder Woman lassoing lightning bolts has my interest and attention. The actors are great, and the director has already earned my regard, so I'm in for a ticket. We'll see next year.
snippet.textOriginal:
Huh...  So much goodness, but there's also so much I question. 

I can't tell what the movie is about.  The first Wonder Woman was about war, and it's nature.  Aquaman was about responsibility, both personal and with family.  Shazam was very much about the experience of having to growing up before you're ready.  From the trailer, I can't tell what this movie is really about thematically.  I can tell some of the plot points...  I can see some of what happens, but that's not the same thing. 

Still, Wonder Woman lassoing lightning bolts has my interest and attention.  The actors are great, and the director has already earned my regard, so I'm in for a ticket.  We'll see next year.
